# Project Structure Guide

## Monorepo Structure

This project uses pnpm workspace + Turborepo monorepo.

- `apps/web/`: Current complete SaaS application (the only app at this stage)
- `packages/`: Future package extraction target (no business packages yet)
- Root: Workspace orchestration, turbo, CI, engineering docs, AI coding rules

## Core Directories (in apps/web)
- `apps/web/src/app/`: Next.js app router pages and layouts
- `apps/web/src/components/`: Reusable React components
- `apps/web/src/lib/`: Utility functions and shared code
- `apps/web/src/db/`: Database schema and migrations using Drizzle ORM
- `apps/web/src/stores/`: Zustand state management
- `apps/web/src/actions/`: Server actions and API routes
- `apps/web/src/hooks/`: Custom React hooks
- `apps/web/src/types/`: TypeScript type definitions
- `apps/web/src/i18n/`: Internationalization setup
- `apps/web/src/mail/`: Email templates and mail functionality
- `apps/web/src/payment/`: Payment integration
- `apps/web/src/credits/`: Credits system
- `apps/web/src/analytics/`: Analytics and tracking
- `apps/web/src/storage/`: File storage integration
- `apps/web/src/notification/`: Sending Notifications
- `apps/web/src/newsletter/`: Newsletter subscription management

## Configuration Files (in apps/web)
- `apps/web/next.config.ts`: Next.js configuration
- `apps/web/drizzle.config.ts`: Database configuration
- `apps/web/components.json`: UI components configuration
- `apps/web/source.config.ts`: Fumadocs source configuration
- `apps/web/postcss.config.mjs`: PostCSS configuration
- `apps/web/tsconfig.json`: TypeScript configuration
- `apps/web/global.d.ts`: Global TypeScript declarations

## Content Management (in apps/web)
- `apps/web/content/`: MDX content files
- `apps/web/messages/`: next-intl i18n message files

## Root Configuration
- `biome.json`: Code formatting and linting rules (workspace-level)
- `tsconfig.base.json`: Base TypeScript configuration (workspace-level)
- `turbo.json`: Turborepo task configuration
- `pnpm-workspace.yaml`: pnpm workspace definition

## Environment
- `env.example`: Environment variables template (root)
- `apps/web/.env`: Application environment variables

## Important Rules
- Current business code only exists in `apps/web`.
- Do NOT create root `src/`, `content/`, or `messages/` directories.
- Do NOT create `apps/admin`, `apps/landing`, `apps/docs`, `apps/worker`, `apps/gateway`, `apps/studio` prematurely.
- Do NOT extract `packages/auth`, `packages/db`, `packages/payment`, `packages/ui` prematurely.
- Package extraction will be done in Phase 2 according to plan.
